"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#custom-tooltip-formatting","content":"Tooltip values formatted with `tooltipValueFormatter` (e.g. currency, units)."},"957":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-64","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#custom-accessors","content":"Custom data shape (e.g. `date`/`value`) with `xAccessor` and `yAccessor`."},"958":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-65","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#missing-values","content":"Null Y values create breaks in the line."},"959":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-66","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#fixed-size","content":"Explicit chart size via `width` and `height` props (e.g. 800×400)."},"960":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-67","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#bitcoin-price","content":"Time-series with date and currency formatting, gridlines, and nice Y-axis."},"961":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-68","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#city-temperature","content":"Multiple series over time with legend, shared time axis, and temperature (°F) formatting."},"962":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-69","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#browser-usage","content":"Categorical X-axis (band scale) with multiple series and percentage formatting."},"963":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-70","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#right-to-left","content":"The chart follows the current **layout direction** (LTR or RTL). By default, that direction is detected automatically from the browser or system settings. When it is RTL, the chart mirrors axes and labels accordingly."},"964":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-71","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#data-attributes","content":"The chart root exposes data attributes that reflect prop state for styling:"},"965":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-72","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#data-attributes","content":"**Chart container:** `data-width`, `data-height`, `data-x-labels`, `data-y-labels`, `data-x-labels-vertical`, `data-x-baseline`, `data-y-baseline`, `data-x-tick-marks`, `data-y-tick-marks`"},"966":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-73","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#component-customization","content":"Use the `className` prop on the chart container to add or override styles:"},"967":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-74","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Provide &#x2A;*`aria-label`** to describe the chart (e.g. \"Monthly sales revenue from January to May 2024\")."},"968":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-75","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"Use &#x2A;*`desc`** for a longer description rendered in the SVG `<desc>` for screen readers."},"969":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-76","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#aria-support","content":"The component sets ARIA attributes on interactive and structural elements as needed."},"970":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-77","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#chart-not-sizing-or-empty","content":"Ensure the chart has a non-zero size. Place it in a container with explicit dimensions or use `width` and `height`:"},"971":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-78","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#dates-not-displaying-correctly","content":"Use `xType=\"time\"` when the X-axis values are Date objects:"},"972":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-79","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#tooltip-or-crosshair-not-showing","content":"Ensure `tooltip`, `showCrosshair`, or `showDataPoints` are not set to `false`, and that the chart receives pointer events (e.g. no overlay blocking hover)."},"973":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-80","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use for trends over time or along a continuous scale."},"974":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-81","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Use when comparing a few series (e.g. 2–5 lines); avoid too many overlapping lines."},"975":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart-82","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/line-chart#when-to-use-linechart","content":"Prefer a single chart with a legend over multiple small charts when comparing the same X range."},"976":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"page","content":"Tooltip","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip"},"977":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","content":"An internal component used for displaying tooltip information in chart components."},"978":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"Features"},"979":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#internal-component","content":"Internal Component"},"980":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#props","content":"Props"},"981":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"Value formatting"},"982":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#examples","content":"Examples"},"983":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#single-series","content":"Single Series"},"984":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#multiple-series","content":"Multiple Series"},"985":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#arrow","content":"Arrow"},"986":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-9","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Multiple series**: Shows all series that have a datum at the hovered X position in a single tooltip."},"987":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-10","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Series matching**: Rows are built from `series` by matching `series[].id` to keys in `tooltipData.datumByKey` (from visx at the hovered X)."},"988":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-11","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#features","content":"**Value formatting**: You can supply a function to format each value; if you don't, the tooltip shows the point's `y` (or nothing when null). Use the formatter for custom data shapes."},"989":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-12","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is intended for use inside chart components."},"990":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-13","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#props","content":"The `Tooltip` component accepts the following props:"},"991":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-14","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Default:** When `formatValue` is not provided, the tooltip uses a formatter that reads the data point’s `y` property (same as the chart's default Y accessor), converts it to a string, and returns an empty string for null. This is correct for the default `DataPoint` shape (`{ x, y }`)."},"992":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-15","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#value-formatting","content":"**Custom:** Pass `formatValue` to control display. The function receives the datum and returns a string. Use it to both extract and format (e.g. currency, percentage, custom units). For custom data point shapes (generic `TooltipProps<YourDatum>`), you must pass `formatValue` because the default only reads `y`."},"993":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-16","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#single-series","content":"Basic tooltip with a single series and default formatting."},"994":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-17","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#multiple-series","content":"Tooltip with multiple series; all series at the same X position are shown together."},"995":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-18","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip#arrow","content":"Use the `showArrow` prop to set whether the tooltip arrow is visible or not."},"996":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"page","content":"TooltipDismissStrip","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip"},"997":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","content":"Internal visx XYChart helper that closes the tooltip when the pointer enters a leading-edge strip over scroll-synced axis chrome"},"998":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"Internal Component"},"999":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"Props"},"1000":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#examples","content":"Examples"},"1001":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Basic"},"1002":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#internal-component","content":"This component is **internal-only** and not exported from the package. It is designed for use within chart components."},"1003":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#props","content":"The `TooltipDismissStrip` component accepts the following props:"},"1004":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/tooltip-dismiss-strip#basic","content":"Tooltip provider, relative container, optional controls to open the visx tooltip and the dismiss strip on the leading edge."},"1005":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"page","content":"useChartColor","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color"},"1006":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","content":"A hook for assigning deterministic, index-based colors to chart series using design token CSS variables. Safe under React concurrent rendering."},"1007":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1008":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#props","content":"Props"},"1009":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#examples","content":"Examples"},"1010":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#single-series","content":"Single series"},"1011":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#multiple-series","content":"Multiple series"},"1012":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Wrap your chart (or list) with `ChartColorProvider`; each component that calls `useChartColor()` receives a CSS variable reference. Indices are assigned in an effect at mount, so allocation is safe under React concurrent rendering and StrictMode. Same component instance keeps the same color; colors cycle after the ninth consumer. No need to pass an index—order in the tree determines assignment."},"1013":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#single-series","content":"One series using the first chart color."},"1014":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color-8","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-chart-color#multiple-series","content":"Multiple series each receiving the next color in sequence."},"1015":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"page","content":"useNormalizedSeries","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series"},"1016":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","content":"A hook that ensures every series config has a stable unique id, generating one from useId when omitted."},"1017":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1018":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-normalized-series#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"Accepts a `SeriesConfig[]` array and returns a memoized copy where each item is guaranteed to have an `id`. When an item has no `id`, one is generated using a component-scoped prefix from React's `useId`, ensuring IDs are unique across multiple chart instances on the same page. Existing `id` values are preserved as-is."},"1019":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"page","content":"useScrollableXYChart","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Chart"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart"},"1020":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-0","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","content":"A hook for scrollable visx XY charts that measures the rendered axes and returns margins, content-sized width and height, scroll offsets, and a vertical-labels flag, so the chart sizes itself to whatever it actually contains."},"1021":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-1","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"For use with chart components (not exported)"},"1022":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-2","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#examples","content":"Examples"},"1023":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-3","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Auto layout"},"1024":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-4","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Inputs.** Wire `parentRef` to the scroll container and `xAxisRef` / `yAxisRef` to the axis groups. Optionally pass `xLabelsOrientation` (`'auto'` | `'horizontal'` | `'vertical'`, default `'auto'`) to force the category-label layout; `'auto'` rotates labels vertical when the visible width can't fit the horizontal-tick footprint plus the Y-axis width."},"1025":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-5","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Outputs.** The hook returns `margin`, `chartWidth`, `chartHeight`, `xLabelsVertical`, `scrollLeft` / `scrollTop`, and `yAxisRect` for the chart to consume. Width and height are sized to whichever is larger — the visible slot or the room the rendered labels need — so the chart grows past the viewport and the parent scrolls when labels demand more space."},"1026":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-6","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#for-use-with-chart-components-not-exported","content":"**Behavior.** Measurement runs through `useParentSize`, a `MutationObserver`, and a `ResizeObserver` on the wired nodes. All axis measurements are batched in one `requestAnimationFrame` and bail out when the result hasn't changed, so a burst of observer fires costs at most one reflow and one render per frame."},"1027":{"id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart-7","page_id":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/chart/use-scrollable-xy-chart#auto-layout","content":"Hook wired to a scrolling parent; scroll or resize to watch the returned values update."},"1028":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"page","content":"Box","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box"},"1029":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"Polymorphic layout component providing consistent spacing, elevation, rounding, and self-alignment"},"1030":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/box#installation","conten